  "description": "Growing protocol for *Rumex sanguineus*, perennial herb producing deep-red-veined foliage and lemony, sour flavor from oxalic acid. Establish from seed; produces harvestable rosette in first year. Longevous perennial (zone 4+); allows multiple harvests per season without replanting. Ornamental foliage value in mixed borders.",
